name: Reebok Ragnar Northwest Passage
intro:
Where the forest meets the sea, Reebok Ragnar Relay Northwest Passage will excite your senses and leave you breathless. The journey begins near the Canadian border in the city of Blaine, WA. Then you will run relay style from point to point as you experience the iconic sights of the Pacific Northwest including the glacial Cascade and Olympic Mountain ranges, Deception Pass and the Puget Sound. As you and your team cover 200 miles of running, vibrant fireweed blossoms light the way through the gently rolling countryside, quaint towns and endless skies that backdrop noble bald eagles soaring above the trees. As you push through the fatigue and final miles of the course, the excitement will grow with each step as you surge to the finish line on Whidbey Island for a celebration you won’t soon forget.  

GREAT NEWS! All 2017 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving free Reebok running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

Reebok Ragnar Northwest Passage is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar Northwest Passage and Ragnar Trail Cascades-WA and earn the Addiction Double Medal.

charity:
Seattle's Union Gospel Mission

Seattle's Union Gospel Mission provides emergency care and long-term recovery services to hurting and homeless people in the greater Seattle area. We're dedicated to serving, rescuing and transforming those in greatest need through the grace of Jesus Christ.

God's calling us to dream big as the gap widens between human need and public resources. We're expanding our efforts like never before — beyond Seattle to the rest of King County.

We started serving soup to thousands of homeless and unemployed people during the Great Depression. More than 80 years later, we're still caring for our neighbors — but in more ways than ever!

 

It Ain't Chemo

It Ain’t Chemo Cancer Warriors is a registered 501 (c)3 based in Nevada that provides comfort packs and resources to people fighting cancer throughout the United States. IAC does not support any one type of cancer or group and takes great pride sending smiles to their Cancer Warriors. IAC founder Kevin Hoyt is a cancer survivor who identified some key items that were not available to him while he was in treatment. Basically he saw his doctors doing great things to battle his disease but not addressing some of the most basic needs that arise when a person is in treatment. Gathering items such as a warm soft blanket, reading materials, hand sanitizer and electronics to aid in keeping Warriors occupied and comfortable during treatment became his mission. Today IAC sends approximately 150 Warrior Packs annually based upon budget availability and has great concept of providing fun experiences for Warriors such as meeting celebrities and taking adventures.

travel.name: Hotel Options
travel.content:
Hotel Options

We have partnered with onPeak to provide you with hotel options for your race. Through this partnership, we are able to offer you the most competitive nightly rates at favorable hotels throughout the city and will strive to provide you with a smooth and effortless booking process when making your travel reservations. Book Early with Our Official Lodging Partner for the Best Selection!

Click HERE to view onPeak's special hotel offers for Reebok Ragnar Northwest Passage participants! 


 

Hampton Inn Bellingham Airport Special Ragnar rate only $114! Book HERE.

All rooms include free WiFi and custom-designed beds, flat-screen TVs with HD channels and coffeemakers. Rooms are equipped with microwaves, minifridges, pull-out sofas and whirlpool tubs. Enjoy a free on-site hot breakfast (daily) and weekday breakfast bags to go, as well as a fitness center, outdoor pool, and free parking. 

 

Van Rental

Need to rent a van? Enterprise can hook you up!

 

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your van into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $20/person for a van of 6!

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, July 11th to ensure delivery before the race!*

GroupLocation.name: Exchange 18
GroupLocation.description:
Attention! Signing up for as a Volunteer for the La Conner shift below does not mean you will be assigned the entire length of this shift. Shifts will be arranged as we get closer to the date.  We are asking for at least a six hour commitment.  Watch for an email soon from your Group Leader so she can get your preference of time and make assignments. 

Volunteers for this shift will cooperatively manage the following tasks: Announce incoming runners as they approach the exchange, record runner arrival times, manage traffic flow (runners and vans), keep parking organized, restock supplies and keep the exchange area free of litter. Note: During set up and clean up, lifting is required, and volunteers for this shift must be able to lift 25-30lbs.

GroupLocation.name: Finish Line
GroupLocation.description:
Volunteers for this shift will be involved with the end of the Finish Line celebration. There will be some greeting of incoming runners as they finish the race. Then the focus will be on cleaning up the area and breaking down tents, inflatables, ensuring the grounds are clean, tying off full trash bags, replenish trash can liners when needed, and making runs to the trailer and dumpster.

Heavy lifting may be involved. You will work with and be very appreciated by Ragnar Staff.  Thank you!!

reg_system.name: Reebok Ragnar Northwest Passage
reg_system.description: Where the forest meets the sea, Reebok Ragnar Relay Northwest Passage will excite your senses and leave you breathless. The journey begins near the Canadian border in the city of Blaine, WA. Then you will run relay style from point to point as you experience the iconic sights of the Pacific Northwest including the glacial Cascade and Olympic Mountain ranges, Deception Pass and the Puget Sound. As you and your team cover 200 miles of running, vibrant fireweed blossoms light the way through the gently rolling countryside, quaint towns and endless skies that backdrop noble bald eagles soaring above the trees. As you push through the fatigue and final miles of the course, the excitement will grow with each step as you surge to the finish line on Whidbey Island for a celebration you won’t soon forget.
